body:
As cool as his voice sounds, the 10 generic lines of VO he has, doesn&#039;t do much to promote lore-immersion...

With his daughter around the corner _(and one would assume he would need specific quotes for her, seeming she is the reason for 90% of his lore)_, and with the whole void theme being forefront atm, this is the time, _there will never be a better reason_ to update his VO. Much like how Nasus&#039; was updated when Azir was released.

So if you don&#039;t do it now, you may find it very hard to find cause in the future.

Kassadin is one of the few assassins I truly love. Unlike many others, his play style functions.. well.. how you&#039;d expect an assassin&#039;s would! He goes ham on one person, deletes them, and then gets the fuck out, and is less useful for a while afterwards. He doesn&#039;t jump in, mash his AoE, then turn into a fighter and duel the survivors, like many of the others do.  Unfortunately for such an awesome play style, playing him feels a bit like a stuck record sometimes:

&quot;On my way.&quot;
&quot;You are null and Void.&quot;
&quot;Your magic is powerless against me.&quot;
&quot;On my way.&quot;
&quot;You are null and Void.&quot;
&quot;Your magic is powerless against me.&quot;

Imo, he would definitely benefit from a new VO _(hopefully with Adam Harrington still, as his voice matches the character so well. and it would be nice especially after Riot outright insulted him and his work in a comment when Ryze was reworked)_.
